result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Rusk County Drug Court Form.  DE to serve 48 hours in jail starting 5/04/16

Defendant Brieel A Zehner in court with attorney Annette M. Barna.  James Jay Rennicke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Heard along with 15CF9, 14CM97, 14CF83, 14CF105, 15CF9.  Case settlement has been reached in all cases.  Court recites case settlements into the court record.  Court instructs on plea questionnaire/waiver of rights.  
14CM97-CASE WILL BE DISMISSED BUT READ IN
14CF83-CASE WILL BE DISMISSED BUT READ IN
14CF105-DE WILL ENTER A PLEA TO CT'S 1,3.  CT'S 2,4 WILL BE DISMISSED BUT READ IN
15CF1-DE WILL ENTER A PLEA TO CT 1.  CT'S 2,3 WILL BE DISMISSED.
15CF9-CASE WILL BE DISMISSED BUT READ IN. 

DE enters a plea of NC to Ct's 1,3 in 14CF105, court will accept and find the DE guilty.  

Sentence will be withheld, two years probation ordered.  DE will pay restitution in the amount of $1598.00 from read in case 14CM97, will complete Drug Court, will complete an AODA assessment, must maintain absolute sobriety, no alcohol possession or consumption, no illicit drug possession or consumption, must maintain some kind of employment or be involved in community service, must enroll in grief counseling, will have day for day credit for time served, DE will be eligible for expunction of both CF and CM cases upon successful completion of cases.  DE waives any PSI.  DE will comply with any conditions imposed by DOC. DE will pay CC.

Defendant Brieel A Zehner in court with attorney Annette M. Barna.  James Jay Rennicke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Heard along with 15CF09.  Motion hearing for bond modification.  State does not object to modification of bond to allow DE to be accepted into the Fresh Start Program.  DE will be allowed huber to participate in the Fresh Start program.  This modifcation will be for all cases.  May be released for work purpose only.
Motion hearing on February 17, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Brieel A Zehner in court with attorney Annette M. Barna.  Defendant Brieel A Zehner in custody.  Rachel Payne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Waive formal reading of Criminal Complaint, will waive time limit and prelim hearing at this time.  Court instructs on waiver of prelim hearing.  Court will find probable cause, will bind over.  Set for arraignment 3-17-15 @ 2:00PM.  Will also waive prelim in 15CF9.  Set both for arraignment same day/time.  Atty would like to address the issue of bond.  DE would like release for child visitation and Access appt.  The court will allow release for supervised visitations of child and appts at Aurora.  DE will comply with all rules of Huber release per the jail.  Will be confined to jail other then these visits.  DE will arrange these times and be responsible for transportation.
